CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper July 13, 1946, pg. 25, reads: "Off to Camp - Camp Achievement will be the mecca for many Pittsburgh boys and girls who wish to take to the great outdoors for the summer season. These lucky kids were snapped as they boarded a bus on Wylie Avenue to take them to camp. The picture was taken on [in] front of the home of Mrs. Alma Illery, president of the Achievement Clubs, sponsor of the camp. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Children boarding Baptist church bus to go to Camp Achievement, Wylie Avenue, Hill District
